# My Project

A CLI tool that converts Markdown files to styled PDF documents.

## Features

- Parse Markdown with full GFM support
- Syntax-highlighted code blocks
- Table of contents generation
- Custom CSS themes
- Watch mode for live preview

## Tech Stack

- Language: Go
- PDF rendering: chromedp (headless Chrome)
- CLI framework: cobra

## Architecture

Single binary with three subcommands:
- `convert` — one-shot Markdown to PDF
- `watch` — file watcher with live reload
- `theme` — manage CSS themes

## Testing

Unit tests for parser, integration tests for PDF output comparison.
